verses.text_plain: Set the trumpet to thy mouth. He shall come as an eagle against the house of the Lord, because they have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law.
verses.verse_html:
1Set the trumpet to thy mouth. He shall come as an eagle against the house of the Lord, because they have transgressed my covenant, and trespassed against my law. ▼
▼ thy: Heb. the roof of thy

footnotes.body_text: ▼ thy: Heb. the roof of thy
footnotes.body_html: ▼ thy: Heb. the roof of thy

verses.text_plain: Israel shall cry unto me, My God, we know thee.
verses.verse_html: 2Israel shall cry unto me, My God, we know thee.

verses.text_plain: Israel hath cast off the thing that is good: the enemy shall pursue him.
verses.verse_html: 3Israel hath cast off the thing that is good: the enemy shall pursue him.

verses.text_plain: They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and I knew it not: of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.
verses.verse_html: 4They have set up kings, but not by me: they have made princes, and I knew it not: of their silver and their gold have they made them idols, that they may be cut off.

tokens.text: but not by me: they have made princes
that they may be cut off

verses.text_plain: Thy calf, O Samaria, hath cast thee off; mine anger is kindled against them: how long will it be ere they attain to innocency?
verses.verse_html: 5Thy calf, O Samaria, hath cast thee off; mine anger is kindled against them: how long will it be ere they attain to innocency?

verses.text_plain: For from Israel was it also: the workman made it; therefore it is not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.
verses.verse_html: 6For from Israel was it also: the workman made it; therefore it is not God: but the calf of Samaria shall be broken in pieces.

verses.text_plain: For they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind: it hath no stalk: the bud shall yield no meal: if so be it yield, the strangers shall swallow it up.
verses.verse_html:
7For they have sown the wind, and they shall reap the whirlwind: it hath no stalk: the bud shall yield no meal: if so be it yield, the strangers shall swallow it up. ▼
▼ stalk: or, standing corn

footnotes.body_html: ▼ stalk: or, standing corn

verses.text_plain: Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a vessel wherein is no pleasure.
verses.verse_html: 8Israel is swallowed up: now shall they be among the Gentiles as a vessel wherein is no pleasure.

tokens.text: now shall they be among the Gentiles

verses.text_plain: For they are gone up to Assyria, a wild ass alone by himself: Ephraim hath hired lovers.
verses.verse_html:
9For they are gone up to Assyria, a wild ass alone by himself: Ephraim hath hired lovers. ▼
▼ lovers: Heb. loves

verses.text_plain: Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes.
verses.verse_html:
10Yea, though they have hired among the nations, now will I gather them, and they shall sorrow a little for the burden of the king of princes. ▼
▼ sorrow: or, begin
 , ▼
▼ a…: or, in a little while

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a…: or, in a little while
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a…: or, in a little while

verses.text_plain: Because Ephraim hath made many altars to sin, altars shall be unto him to sin.
verses.verse_html: 11Because Ephraim hath made many altars to sin, altars shall be unto him to sin.

tokens.text: shall be unto him to sin

verses.text_plain: I have written to him the great things of my law, but they were counted as a strange thing.
verses.verse_html: 12I have written to him the great things of my law, but they were counted as a strange thing.

verses.text_plain: They sacrifice flesh for the sacrifices of mine offerings, and eat it; but the Lord accepteth them not; now will he remember their iniquity, and visit their sins: they shall return to Egypt.
verses.verse_html:
13They sacrifice flesh for the sacrifices of mine offerings, and eat it; but the Lord accepteth them not; now will he remember their iniquity, and visit their sins: they shall return to Egypt. ▼
▼ They sacrifice…: or, In the sacrifices of mine offerings they, etc

tokens.text: them not; now will he remember

footnotes.body_text: ▼ They sacrifice…: or, In the sacrifices of mine offerings they, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ They sacrifice…: or, In the sacrifices of mine offerings they, etc

verses.text_plain: For Israel hath forgotten his Maker, and buildeth temples; and Judah hath multiplied fenced cities: but I will send a fire upon his cities, and it shall devour the palaces thereof.
verses.verse_html: 14For Israel hath forgotten his Maker, and buildeth temples; and Judah hath multiplied fenced cities: but I will send a fire upon his cities, and it shall devour the palaces thereof.
